<LP>
   SHREVEPORT, La. -- Arkla Exploration Co. said it tested an
oil and gas well in southwestern Mississippi.
   The independent oil and natural gas producer said its
Neyland Heirs No. 1 well flowed at a daily rate of 360
barrels of oil and 458,000 cubic feet of natural gas from
depths of between 12,041 and 12,051 feet.
