<HL>
   UAL's United Airlines Traffic
</HL>
<DATE>
04/05/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   UAL
</CO>
<IN>
AIRLINES (AIR)
</IN>
<LP>
   CHICAGO -- UAL Corp. said March traffic at its United
Airlines unit climbed 4.5% to 6.31 billion revenue passenger
miles from 6.04 billion miles a year earlier.
   A revenue passenger mile is one paying passenger flown one
mile.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The carrier's load factor, or the percentage of seats
filled, dropped in March to 67.7% from the year-earlier
68.8%.
   International traffic increased 27% in the latest month,
while traffic at its much-larger domestic segment slipped
1.4%.
   For the year to date, United's traffic was 17.07 billion
revenue passenger miles, up 6.4% from 16.04 billion miles a
year earlier. Load factor for the year to date was 64.9%, up
from 63.5%.
   United's international traffic increased 32% in the latest
year-to-date, while its domestic traffic was essentially
flat.
</TEXT>
