<LP>
   The following were among yesterday's offerings and
pricings in U.S. and non-U.S. capital markets, with terms and
syndicate manager, as compiled by Dow Jones Capital Markets
Report:
                                                                                                       

                         CORPORATE
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   Cyprus Minerals Co. -- $150 million of notes, due April 1,
2002, was priced at par to yield 10.125%. The non-callable
notes were priced at a spread of 151 basis points above the
Treasury's 10-year note. Rated Baa-2 by Moody's Investors
Service Inc. and triple-B by Standard &amp; Poor's Corp., the
issue will be sold through underwriters led by First Boston
Corp.
   Lousiana Power &amp; Light Co. -- $100 million of first
mortgage bonds, due April 1, 2020, was won in competitive
bidding by a group led by Salomon Brothers Inc. The bonds
will be reoffered at 98.125 to yield 10.33%, or a spread of
174 basis points above the Treasury's bellwether bond. The
issue, which is non-refundable for five years, is rated Baa-3
by Moody's and triple-B by S&amp;P.
                                                                                                       

                        MUNICIPALS
                                                                                                       

   New Jersey -- $350 million various full faith and credit
general obligation bonds, due April 1, 1992-2011, apparently
were won by a Goldman Sachs &amp; Co. group. The bonds, rated
triple-A by both Moody's and S&amp;P, were priced for reoffering
to yield from 6.10% in 1992 to 7.10% in 2010 and 2011.
