</IN>
<GV>
JUSTICE DEPARTMENT (JUS)
</GV>
<LP>
   Consolidated Rail Corp. said it received a permanent
injunction, barring the Brotherhood of Maintenance of Way
Employees from striking the freight railroad.
   Philadelphia-based Conrail said a federal court in
Pennsylvania ruled that current talks on a new labor contract
conformed with the Railway Labor Act and that the threatened
strike violated a provision of the law.
</LP>
