   The union represents 6,000 employees who maintain
Conrail's tracks. Jeff Zeh, international president of the
Detroit-based union, said that "obviously we're
disappointed."
   Mr. Zeh objected to what he called "the slow pace" of the
negotiations, and he said that Conrail's plan to restructure
-- including a stock buy-back, an employee stock ownership
plan, and work-force cuts -- would hurt the union.
