<LP>
   Air Products &amp; Chemicals Inc. said a subsidiary acquired
options on a 5.9% stake of Carburos Metalicos S.A., which, if
exercised, would boost Air Products' share of the Spanish
industrial gas and metal concern to about 30%.
   The Allentown, Pa., company said that the cost and
exercise price of the options, which are exercisable over the
next four years, would involve a transaction of about $75
million at current exchange rates. Air Products received
immediate voting rights for the optioned shares.
</LP>
